(this["webpackJsonppersonal-site"]=this["webpackJsonppersonal-site"]||[]).push([[6],{158:function(e,n,t){"use strict";t.r(n);var a=t(0),r=t(157),o=(t(1),t(5)),s=t(77),i=t.n(s),d=t(19),l="\n# Intro\n\nI have 10 years experience in corporate strategy, corporate and business development, product management, and business valuation. I am currently helping grow new connected car data services businesses at [Ford](https://ford.com) while pursuing a graduate degree in computer science. If you think I can be helpful to you or would like to meet me, please feel free to get in touch.\n\n# Currently\n\nAt Ford, I have learned how to help create new businesses within a large established organization, manage people, develop relationships with customers, and partner with global teams on large scale strategic initiatives. A large part of my work entails rolling up my sleeves with numbers in order to build business cases and develop strategic views for new connected car data products and services.  My team also supports the execution of new services and data product launches within Ford. \n\x3c!---\n# Some fun history\n\n- At age 6 I started playing soccer and continued to play each year through high school.\n\n- My parents purchased our first computer in 1993 when I was 7. It was a Macintosh Performa. My favorite games were Escape Velocity, Sid Meier's Colonization, and Civilization 2. Some of the other more educational favorites were Treasure MathStorm, The Oregon Trail 2, and Museum Madness.\n\n- At 8 years old I saw the Chargers make it to the Superbowl and lose to the 49ers.\n\n- Our family upgraded and got our first PC when I was 11.  It was 1997 and games like Age of Empires and Dark Forces 2: Jedi Knight were released. I discovered the joys of online gaming on the zone.com started subscribing to PC Gamer magazine.\n\n- At 12 years old in 1998 I saw the Padres win the NL Pennant and promptly lose 0-4 to the Yankees in the World Series.\n\n- At 13 in 1999 I went to sleepaway summer camp. Yo-yo's were a very big deal in my life that summer and the US Women's National Soccer Team won the World Cup.\n\n- At age 15 after saving allowance money from mowing the lawn I was able to build my first PC. My favorite store was Fry's and I learned that Athlon processors were easier to overclock. The prize possession of my build was a 128 MB ATI graphics card. The Lakers completed their 3-peat.\n\n- At age 16, I learned why you keep the case screwed on when the computer is turned on when I fried my motherboard at a LAN party. \n\n- At 19, I started college and experienced seasons for the first time in Hanover, New Hampshire. I fondly remember getting up at 7 am to leave my dorm to go to drill Spanish language classes in heavy snow.\n\n- At 21, in 2008 I interned at Qualcomm over the summer. I started playing golf.  Torrey Pines hosted the US Open that year and I got to see Tiger Woods for the first time as he won the tournament.\n\n- At 22, in 2009 I graduated and moved back to California to enter the real world.  I started my first job working at BeyondTrust, an enterprise security software company based out of Agoura Hills.\n\n- At 28 in 2015, I became a student again, moved to Berkeley, and met my future wife. Our favorite restaurants in Berkeley were Jupiter, Ippudo, Ippuku, and Berkeley Social Club. I was really into Cal basketball and went to all the home games that season with my friends.\n\n- At 29 in 2016, I started to learn to code while interning at Ford over the summer. At 30 I joined Ford full time after graduating from Haas in 2017.\n\n- At 32 I started getting my computer science degree online.\n\n- At 34 in 2021, I moved back to San Diego and published this site.\n---\x3e\n# I like\n\n- 80's and new wave music\n- Sous vide cooking\n- Running\n- Golfing\n- Music trivia\n- Chargers, Lakers, Padres, and Manchester United sports (new convert!)\n\n# Travel / Geography\n\n- I am from originally from San Diego but I have also lived in Berkeley, Agoura Hills, Hanover, Dearborn, and Davis.\n- In 2006, I visited Canada.\n- In 2016, I visited Japan.\n- In 2017, I visited Spain, Italy, and Kazakhstan.\n- In 2018, I visited United Arab Emirates.\n- In 2019, I visited India.\n",c=l.split(/\s+/).map((function(e){return e.replace(/\W/g,"")})).filter((function(e){return e.length})).length,h=function(e){var n=Object.assign({},e);return Object(a.jsx)(o.b,Object(r.a)({},n))};n.default=function(){return Object(a.jsx)(d.a,{title:"About",description:"Learn about John Hentrich",children:Object(a.jsxs)("article",{className:"post markdown",id:"about",children:[Object(a.jsx)("header",{children:Object(a.jsxs)("div",{className:"title",children:[Object(a.jsx)("h2",{"data-testid":"heading",children:Object(a.jsx)(o.b,{to:"/about",children:"About Me"})}),Object(a.jsxs)("p",{children:["(in about ",c," words)"]})]})}),Object(a.jsx)(i.a,{source:l,renderers:{Link:h},escapeHtml:!1})]})})}}}]);
